title: A Memphian's trip to Europe with Cook's educational party:
author: Watson, Samuel. [from old catalog]
snippet: It was in this vicinity — Huntingdon — that Oliver Cromwell was born, April 25, 1699, and was baptized four days afterward, as appears from the parish register. The house is now called the Cromwell House.
